    <title>more folds</title>
    <content type='html'>&lt;div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"&gt;&lt;a href="https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/img/b/R29vZ2xl/AVvXsEi0Te0USt6v5ldL38U64J3y1AUA7cvfo6JqEM7uS_kLw1B_ruGGtrhgruwQkDQUmyC0Codwqb0KRz9pi9ZbX0zuetZiGgsrKMPUKbnzaaoHJcVBn4w8OoTVMJSB56sIWiXDuxGKwN6rVsk/s1600-h/blintz.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"&gt;&lt;img border="0" src="https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/img/b/R29vZ2xl/AVvXsEi0Te0USt6v5ldL38U64J3y1AUA7cvfo6JqEM7uS_kLw1B_ruGGtrhgruwQkDQUmyC0Codwqb0KRz9pi9ZbX0zuetZiGgsrKMPUKbnzaaoHJcVBn4w8OoTVMJSB56sIWiXDuxGKwN6rVsk/s320/blintz.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
PBS has launched &lt;a href="http://www.pbs.org/independentlens/between-the-folds/index.html"&gt;a new&lt;b&gt; Between the Folds&lt;/b&gt; website&lt;/a&gt; - the &lt;a href="http://www.pbs.org/independentlens/between-the-folds/match-the-folds.html"&gt;online quiz&lt;/a&gt; where you have to match the crease pattern to a finished model is neat.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
I've mentioned &lt;b&gt;&lt;a href="http://greenfusefilms.com/"&gt;Between the Folds&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/b&gt;in previous posts (&lt;a href="http://mathrecreation.blogspot.com/2009/10/another-origami-ideal.html"&gt;here&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href="http://mathrecreation.blogspot.com/2009/08/origami.html"&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;)&amp;nbsp;- if you haven't seen it yet and you get PBS, you really should check it out.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
A lot of the origami models featured in the film can also be seen in &lt;a href="http://www.origami-usa.org/art_gallery"&gt;Origami USA's gallery&lt;/a&gt;. If you are looking for something to fold after watching the film, you should check out the &lt;a href="http://www.origami-usa.org/diagrams"&gt;diagrams&lt;/a&gt; from Origami USA as well.</content>
